{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"22f7ed9a-303f-4bfa-ae35-1fac2796b350","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Event flow:**\n\n| Transition | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | Created → Activated |\n| Sent to background | Deactivated → Stopped (→ Backgrounding on iOS/Mac) |\n| Returned to foreground | Resumed → Activated |\n| App closed | Destroying |\n\n> `Backgrounding` is iOS/Mac Catalyst only — use it to save state. On Android/Windows it won't fire.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4dd066e2-fe97-4418-9e54-31accfb41937","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about subscribing to Window lifecycle events in a .NET MAUI app for debugging/logging purposes. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI that I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the `Window` class exposes several lifecycle events that correspond to the app's state transitions. Let me provide a concise, helpful answer.\n\nThe Window lifecycle events in .NET MAUI are:\n- Created\n- Activated\n- Deactivated\n- Stopped\n- Resumed\n- Destroying\n- Backgrounding (iOS/Mac Catalyst)\n\n\nNow I'll show a code example demonstrating how to hook into these events for logging purposes.","outputTokens":497,"requestId":"E82F:29C906:25CF536:29DC6F5:69F93F28"},"id":"d2629d0a-7e2c-47df-b3e8-1b6b00d96e87","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:52:02.733Z","parentId":"7ad0b856-e438-4adf-b469-ae745211c813"}
